msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid " functions can optionally return a value to the code calling it.\""
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid "An increment is the amount by which a value changes in your code."
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid "In computer programming, instructions are a single operation the computer recognizes and can execute"
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid " an addition, or assigning a value to a variable.\""
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid "Variables are a tool to give a name to values you want to store in your code and change over time"
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid " you want it to go down. When healing, you want the health to go back up."
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid "You can create a variable named [code]health[/code] to represent the health."
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid " the computer will fetch the corresponding value in its memory for you."
msgstr ""

#: course/glossary.csv
msgid " in that case, a new value.\""
msgstr ""

